The paper deals with reinforcement learning and Markov decision processes, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the detection of corrupt states, which is relevant to the sub-field of computer security (cs.CR). The use of algorithms to solve the problem falls under the sub-field of robotics (cs.RO), and the formalism of CRMDPs is related to the sub-field of control systems (cs.SY).
